<h2>Manage accessibility statements</h2>

<p>Accessibility statements are legally required documents that explain how accessible your product is and how users can report accessibility issues.</p>

<h3>What is an accessibility statement?</h3>
<p>An accessibility statement is a public document that:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Explains your commitment to accessibility</li>
    <li>Describes known accessibility issues</li>
    <li>Provides contact information for reporting problems</li>
    <li>Meets legal requirements for public sector websites and apps</li>
</ul>

<h3>Generating a hosted statement</h3>
<ol>
    <li>Navigate to <strong>Apps → Accessibility Issues and Statements</strong></li>
    <li>Select your enrolled product</li>
    <li>Go to the <strong>Statement</strong> tab</li>
    <li>Click <strong>Generate Statement</strong></li>
    <li>The system will create a statement using templates and current issue data</li>
    <li>Your statement will be available at: <code>https://accessibility-statements.education.gov.uk/s/{FipsId}</code></li>
</ol>

<h3>Statement content</h3>
<p>The generated statement includes:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Product information and commitment</li>
    <li>WCAG compliance status</li>
    <li>Known accessibility issues (from tracked issues)</li>
    <li>Non-accessible content (issues marked as "won't fix")</li>
    <li>Contact information for complaints</li>
    <li>Preparation date and review schedule</li>
</ul>

<h3>Verifying statement installation</h3>
<p>After generating a statement, you need to verify it's linked from your product:</p>
<ol>
    <li>Go to the <strong>Settings</strong> tab for your product</li>
    <li>Enter your <strong>Live Product URL</strong></li>
    <li>Click <strong>Verify Statement</strong></li>
    <li>The system will automatically check if the statement link is present</li>
    <li>If automatic verification fails (e.g., behind authentication), you can <strong>Manually Verify</strong></li>
</ol>

<h3>Statement settings</h3>
<p>In the <strong>Settings</strong> tab, you can configure:</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>SLA Response Days:</strong> How quickly you'll respond to complaints</li>
    <li><strong>Complaint Contact Email:</strong> Where users should send accessibility complaints</li>
    <li><strong>WCAG Target Version:</strong> Target WCAG version (e.g., 2.1, 2.2)</li>
    <li><strong>WCAG Target Level:</strong> Target compliance level (A, AA, or AAA)</li>
    <li><strong>Statement URL:</strong> Link to the hosted statement</li>
    <li><strong>Product URL:</strong> Live product URL for verification</li>
</ul>

<h3>Updating statements</h3>
<p>Statements should be updated when:</p>
<ul>
    <li>New accessibility issues are identified</li>
    <li>Issues are resolved</li>
    <li>Compliance status changes</li>
    <li>Contact information changes</li>
    <li>Regular review periods (typically annually)</li>
</ul>
<p>To update, simply regenerate the statement - it will automatically include the latest issue data.</p>

<h3>Statement dashboard indicators</h3>
<p>The accessibility dashboard shows:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Products with missing statements</li>
    <li>Statements that fail verification</li>
    <li>Products requiring statement updates</li>
    <li>Overdue reviews</li>
</ul>

